         Why cant we have both zoneable pets and have the dot stacking issue fixed? Everyone seems to think or has been taught to think by VI our class should always trade off on something. Dots stacking and zoneable pets are both important to our class. If not from a playablity standpoint then what about respect for our class? </P><P>I was disgusted when I installed sol and found out only BL and Wizards had "pets" that could zone. <b>ALL</b> the pet classes should have had this ability from the start of eq. But now the only 2 that actually need their pets Nec/Mages are still trying to figure out a way they can comprimise with VI to get what they deserve. (i excluded BL from "need" because their pets zone... hell have our pet buff drop on zone whatever thats fine)</P><P>This isn't a flame I have just gotten tired of reading why the we don't deserve fixes to problems that shouldn't exist to begin with. <BR>The most recent changes to pets are wonderfull now lets keep the ball rolling. <BR>Lune</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
