        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I don't think it was possible before.  It might be possible now, sort of.</P><P>The "pets" that zone are, I believe, static level and predefined name.  When the owner zones, the pet dies, but as a "buff" it gets automatically recast upon entrance to the next zone.</P><P>Since our pets were variable level and variable name, even if there were a flag that said "owner zoned with pet, summon a new one when they arrive" it would have a different name and could be a different level.  Now it would be the same level, but you'd zone with Jabobtik and come back with Gebn (with no buffs and no weapons).</P><P>Do familiars and beastlord pets take up a buff slot?  If so, that's the flag that determines whether the new pet NPC is summoned on zone in.  Personally, I don't want my pet taking up another buff slot.</P><P>Do beastlord pets and familiars heal to full when they zone (presumably due to recast)?  If so, then no, we're never going to see our pets zone.  Too easy to exploit.</P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=247832" target="_blank">Morty Undercrypt</a>, Keeper of the <a href="http://www.necrognomicon.com/" target="_blank">NecroGnomicon</a><BR><font size=1>"I am the truth, and the truth shall make you flee."</font id=size1><BR>E'ci<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
